title: ZUCCHINI CASSEROLE
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion and a little salt and pepper; drain the fat. Put the meat in a large, greased casserole, 3 quarts or larger. Sauté the zucchini and mushrooms until almost tender; season lightly and add to the ground beef in the casserole. Prepare the mushroom soup and stir into meat and vegetable mixture along with the cheese; adjust the seasoning if necessary. Bake at 350ē 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
ingredients: 6 small zucchini, sliced in half moons, 24 ounces
1 batch Dottie's Cream of Mushroom Soup for Recipes
